3
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:26,230
Thank you, everyone.

4
00:00:27,030 --> 00:00:28,760
Thank you all for coming.

5
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:32,640
I am very pleased to welcome everyone
to the signing event

6
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:35,670
for my new book, "Haunted Love."

7
00:00:35,670 --> 00:00:38,110
I am the author, Guan Qiao.

8
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,200
Before the official release,

9
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,710
I'd like to say a few words.

10
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:46,320
Recently, many people
have been asking me,

11
00:00:46,390 --> 00:00:50,150
what exactly is magical realism?

12
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:51,960
It's not simply about

13
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:53,920
magic or fantasy.

14
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:57,520
Rather, it's a creative genre.

15
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:59,430
It's more of a tool

16
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:02,560
than a form of literature, like a knife,

17
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,790
like a bow and arrow.

18
00:01:03,790 --> 00:01:06,230
Like an arrow deeply piercing

19
00:01:06,230 --> 00:01:08,040
the rough leather of reality.

20
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:11,040
Magical realism literature
has two characteristics.

21
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:12,480
One is reality,

22
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:16,840
and the other is deep irony.

23
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:22,950
As such, it requires the creator

24
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:25,430
to have ample life experience.

25
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,280
Hey kid, what are you doing?

26
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:30,310
I'm talking to you.

27
00:01:31,510 --> 00:01:35,870
[Haunted Love]
What kind of nonsense is this?

28
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:43,120
What are you even writing?

29
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,430
Ma, is your scale broken?

30
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:46,480
So many books!

31
00:01:47,150 --> 00:01:47,870
80.

32
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:52,310
Buy it or don't.

33
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:58,150
Shandan flowers are blooming, oh...

34
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:00,200
Editor Zhao.

35
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,230
Who's Guan Qiao? I'm Guan Qiao!

36
00:02:03,430 --> 00:02:04,710
Where's my manuscript fee?

37
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,000
Didn't we agree?

38
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,080
What good are those piles
of books to me?

39
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:10,710
We weighed them, 80 yuan.

40
00:02:10,910 --> 00:02:12,190
What did we agree on?

41
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,710
We had a deal.

42
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:14,310
You...

43
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:16,310
You...

44
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:17,960
Hello?

45
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:20,590
Author Guan?

46
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:22,870
Author Guan?

47
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,430
Are you selling?

48
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,140
[Haunted Love]

49
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:03,760
[Sandstorm]
[Episode 4]

50
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,920
Why are you sleeping here?

51
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:33,800
I came to rest for a bit.

52
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:35,040
Finished reading?

53
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,240
I'm a slow reader.

54
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,560
Did you finish it all?

55
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,070
I looked it up.

56
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,680
Back then, there was a forum online

57
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:45,720
specifically discussing bizarre cases.

58
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,560
Guan Qiao posted

59
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,750
his serial there.

60
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:51,120
The serial was set in Kulu.

61
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,870
The victim's name was Cheng Chun.

62
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:56,390
This post gained a lot of attention

63
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,950
on that forum back then.

64
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,800
A publisher found Guan Qiao,

65
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,160
got the rights, and changed the names.

66
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:05,040
They compiled it into a novel.

67
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,510
Many details in the novel

68
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:08,750
were from the case back then

69
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,160
that we hadn’t made public.

70
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,070
So,

71
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:12,920
I think Guan Qiao might know

72
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,950
something we don’t.

73
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,920
What’s your plan?

74
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,680
Talk to him.

75
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,720
Sure.

76
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,720
I’ll nap for another ten minutes.

77
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:27,040
Alright, nap away.

78
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:33,920
I just got back

79
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:36,870
from a book signing.

80
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:39,920
I’m really lacking inspiration now.

81
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:43,360
I think you'd be perfect

82
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:45,310
as the protagonist in my next book.

83
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:49,120
You remind me a lot
of my last girlfriend.

84
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,040
Really?

85
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,720
Really.

86
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,720
You can visit my place sometime.

87
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,750
We could

88
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,920
create together.

89
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,920
I also have some journalist friends
from the province.

90
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:07,070
They’re all in this field.

91
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:09,070
I’ll ask them to interview you too.

92
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:11,310
Aren't you well connected?

93
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,680
You sure know a lot of people.

94
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:28,720
Guan Qiao.

95
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:30,950
We need to talk.

96
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:32,680
Come with us.

97
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:34,120
What is it?

98
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:42,430
I object.

99
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,600
I was just getting a foot massage
at the foot spa.

100
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:46,720
Then suddenly, two people came in

101
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,870
and brought me here.

102
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,800
How was I supposed to know
whether that place

103
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,160
was legitimate or not?

104
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:53,630
We’re not here to talk
about foot massages.

105
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,750
We brought you in

106
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,560
to ask about something else.

107
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,310
Please sit.

108
00:07:01,950 --> 00:07:03,630
You live with Sun Caiyun, right?

109
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,920
Yeah, we’re cohabiting.

110
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,830
But that’s consensual between us.

111
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,120
We writers tend to be romantic.

112
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,120
But I’ve never done anything illegal.

113
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:18,070
Who said you did anything illegal?

114
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:19,720
Then why arrest me?

115
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,310
I’ve read your "Sandstorm".

116
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,720
It’s really well written.

117
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,360
Officer Luo,

118
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:31,310
I’m flattered.

119
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,870
Thank you for your high praise.

120
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,920
Especially the details,
they’re incredibly vivid.

121
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:38,950
Officer Luo,

122
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:40,870
you truly understand me.

123
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,630
When I was writing this work,

124
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:44,720
I put a lot of energy into it.

125
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:46,950
I poured my emotions into it,

126
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,630
and after I finished,
I fell seriously ill.

127
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,950
It wasn’t that simple, was it?

128
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,560
Of course, it wasn’t that simple.

129
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,560
After the book came out, many people
tried to dig up my identity.

130
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:58,310
My fans all know I’m a technical worker.

131
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:01,310
Some even called me
“the next Liu Cixin”,

132
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,920
that sci-fi writer.

133
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,560
They underestimated me.

134
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,480
How can sci-fi even compare...

135
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,510
Do you know Cheng Chun?

136
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:13,870
The female protagonist
in your novel, Chun,

137
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:16,950
resembles the real Cheng Chun.

138
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,510
And your character Chen Yuanbao

139
00:08:19,950 --> 00:08:21,680
closely mirrors the real Ding Baoyuan.

140
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,600
Their professions
and social relationships

141
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,800
are eerily similar.

142
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:26,870
How do you explain that?

143
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:29,680
That case was so sensational.

144
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:32,320
It was all over the newspapers
and the internet.

145
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,360
Which newspapers or websites

146
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,320
ever mentioned Ding Baoyuan
and Cheng Chun having an affair?

147
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:46,510
Guan Qiao,

148
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:48,440
based on your novel,

149
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,550
your love for Cheng Chun
turned into hatred,

150
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,840
or rather, a desire to possess her.

151
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,550
You felt she betrayed you,

152
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:57,360
so you decided to kill Cheng Chun

153
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,150
and frame Ding Baoyuan for it.

154
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,000
Then,

155
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,790
during one of Ding Baoyuan
and Cheng Chun’s secret meetings,

156
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,480
you secretly made a copy of the key
to the heating station

157
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,150
that Ding Baoyuan always carried
on his belt loop.

158
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,030
You then used Ding Baoyuan’s name

159
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,910
to lure Cheng Chun
to the heating station.

160
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:15,240
You killed Cheng Chun
outside the station,

161
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,510
and then used the fabricated key

162
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:20,080
to carry her body inside
and stuff it into the furnace.

163
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:23,150
After that, you used
one of your book fans,

164
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,910
Sun Caiyun, who happens
to be Ding Baoyuan’s wife,

165
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,270
to frame Ding Baoyuan.

166
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:30,080
It's just a novel, Officer Luo.

167
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,240
It’s fiction, a work of imagination.

168
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,790
But you wrote it in the first person,

169
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:35,200
saying you were the one
who killed Cheng Chun

170
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,750
and framed Ding Baoyuan.

171
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:39,840
I had to write it that way
to get readers.

172
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,080
Only by writing it like that
could I get clicks.

173
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:46,000
Look, English novelist Defoe's

174
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,360
"Robinson Crusoe",

175
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,360
Japanese novelist Murakami's
"Norwegian Wood",

176
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,480
and Chinese novelist Liu's
"The Wandering Earth".

177
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,510
They all wrote in the first person.

178
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,670
You have to write that way
for readers to care.

179
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:58,000
You think we could really put
an engine on Earth?

180
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,120
It's all nonsense.

181
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,120
Cheng Chun was murdered,

182
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:03,720
and the original suspect, Ding Baoyuan,

183
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:05,320
has been exonerated.

184
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:08,630
I’ve now listed you as a prime suspect.

185
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,320
On what grounds?

186
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,720
Do you have any evidence?

187
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,510
Do you know Cheng Chun?

188
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,120
Yes, I know her.

189
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,480
How do you know her? Tell me.

190
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,790
She had a stall at the night market.

191
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,480
She sold spicy hotpot.

192
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:28,320
She was quite pretty.

193
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,600
At the time, I was a young artist,

194
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,910
really poor, barely surviving.

195
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,480
I met her at her stall.

196
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,150
When she found out I was a writer,

197
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,200
she started flirting with me.

198
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,240
One thing led to another,
and we got together.

199
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,910
She seduced me first.

200
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,390
So, how did you feel about Cheng Chun?

201
00:10:44,390 --> 00:10:46,360
Is it like what you wrote in your novel?

202
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,440
Hatred born from love,
filled with possessiveness?

203
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,720
She seduced me first.

204
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,720
I’m a writer.

205
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:56,000
I told her I came to Kulu

206
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,670
to find inspiration for my novel.

207
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,720
Once I found it, I’d return
to the provincial city.

208
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:02,670
After hearing that,
she was totally into me.

209
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:03,720
Later,

210
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:07,080
I heard that Cheng Chun
was involved in prostitution.

211
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,360
That’s when we ended things.

212
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:13,240
And then I heard that
Cheng Chun was dead,

213
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:16,480
and you guys arrested Ding Baoyuan.

214
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,720
Everyone in the streets was
talking about it at the time.

215
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,240
There were all kinds of rumors.

216
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:26,120
I figured if I wrote a book about it,
it would definitely be a hit.

217
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:30,910
So I wrote the novel from the
perspective of the murderer

218
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,030
and serialized it online.

219
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,670
I did it all

220
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,750
out of my love for literature.

221
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:41,320
Cheng Chun’s death has absolutely
nothing to do with me.

222
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:43,480
Guan Qiao,

223
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,870
what’s the connection
between Chen Yuanbao and Chun

224
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,120
in real life?

225
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,720
Are you referring to Ding Baoyuan
and Cheng Chun?

226
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,480
They were together for a while,

227
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:57,510
then Sun Caiyun stepped in.

228
00:11:57,630 --> 00:11:58,870
That’s all I know.

229
00:12:01,630 --> 00:12:02,440
Guan Qiao,

230
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,150
you'd better think carefully.

231
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:07,550
Is there anything else
you haven’t told us?

232
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,480
If we find out you’re
withholding information,

233
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,030
it won’t be this easy next time.

234
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,720
That’s really all I know.

235
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,200
In my book,

236
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,270
some parts were things
Cheng Chun told me,

237
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:19,870
and other parts

238
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:21,750
were pieced together from the internet.

239
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,480
That’s all I know, I swear.

240
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:26,320
We should re-interrogate
Ding Baoyuan immediately.

241
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,840
A novel can’t be used
as evidence, can it?

242
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,200
We don’t have any evidence
besides the novel.

243
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,320
So what do you suggest?

244
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,510
You’re the leader.
I’ll follow your lead.

245
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:40,240
Chief Wang, you’re here.

246
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:41,360
Let me introduce you.

247
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,670
Chief Wang, I’m Chen Jianghe.

248
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:44,750
It's great to finally meet you.

249
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:47,030
Jianghe,

250
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,790
take a look at this for me.

251
00:12:52,030 --> 00:12:52,750
What is it?

252
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:54,360
It was tucked inside the files

253
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,440
of the 226 homicide case.

254
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,240
It doesn’t match the evidence list.

255
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,320
It looks familiar.

256
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:03,120
I’ve seen it somewhere before.

257
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,150
Could it have been
mistakenly placed here

258
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:08,240
from another case?

259
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:10,320
No, that’s impossible.

260
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:12,000
No way.

261
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:12,720
Luo,

262
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:13,910
you and Jianghe

263
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,550
should carefully investigate
this case again.

264
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,200
Got it.

265
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,840
Chief Wang, if you're free,

266
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,910
I can treat you to the
best noodles in town.

267
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:33,870
It looks familiar.

268
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,510
Where have I seen it before?

269
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:41,840
Perhaps

270
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,550
there was a mix-up?

271
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:45,150
Before we archive cases,

272
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:47,030
we thoroughly check everything.

273
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,670
Besides the original files
